summary: Ok, same question, but with Phil: what do you think is the most annoying thing he has ever done?
question: Ok, same question, but with Phil: what do you think is the most annoying thing he has ever done?
answer: The first thing that comes to mind is his persona/branding and how man-childish it can be, but actually I don’t think that’s what’s most annoying to me. While I think it’s a bit stale now and he is getting too old for it, there are quite a few of his videos that I really like and before YouTube killed them, I counted his interactive adventures among my favorite videos on the platform (to give some perspective, his Interactive Christmas Adventure ranked higher than any Dan video for me). I think, the most annoying thing about Phil (and also the reason I’ve never been able to get into him as much as Dan) is that he doesn’t ever share his opinions. I especially don’t like it when Dan gets backlash for things that also involve him or that he obviously agrees with and he remains silent. I also hated when he would just give up at the first sign of a game being slightly challenging on the gaming channel (either not take it seriously, outright veto it like he did with Cuphead, or just give up in a way that’s unsatisfying to the audience like he tried to get Dan to do with the Sans battle). As for singular events, I was irrationally annoyed when Phil said he was too sensitive to watch The Handmaid’s Tale. Umm Phil, try being a woman and actually having to deal with misogyny on a daily basis! If you aren’t harrowed by Game of Thrones, you should be able to handle The Handmaid’s Tale, especially as a man, since almost all of the violence in that show is against women (I like both shows and could write an essay on this). Yes, I do get the irony in the fact that I just said I was annoyed that he doesn’t give opinions and then said that I was annoyed by his opinion - I did say it was a bit irrational! I guess what it comes down to is that I have a hard time relating to Phil since I don’t think he ever shows us who he really is, even though I like him enough to be interested in wanting to find out if he ever decided to get a bit more real. I did get serious rage with him on the gaming channel a few times though!
